📌 Project Overview
This Power BI dashboard provides a comprehensive analysis of over 5 years of sales and financial data across 5 major product categories. It delivers meaningful business insights that help stakeholders make data-driven decisions.

🎯 Objectives
Visualize sales trends over time

Identify top-performing categories and products

Analyze cost structures (freight, manufacturing, deductions)

Forecast future sales performance

Enable actionable decisions through interactive filtering

📂 Dataset Highlights
Feature	Description
Duration	5+ Years
Categories	5 Product Categories
Metrics	Sales, Orders, Gross Profit, Freight Cost, Manufacturing Cost, Forecasts, Deductions (Pre/Post Invoice)

📈 Dashboard Components
KPI Cards: Total Sales, Gross Profit, Order Count, Net Deductions

Bar Chart: Top 10 Performing Products by Revenue

Line Charts: Sales Trend Over Years, Forecasted Sales

Pie/Donut Chart: Revenue Distribution by Category

Filters: Year, Product Category, Region

💡 Key Insights
📈 Sales Trend: Consistent annual growth

🏆 Top Category: [Insert category name] leads in revenue

💸 Freight Cost: Notable spikes in specific years

🔮 Forecasting: Predicted 8% growth in next year sales

💼 Business Decisions Enabled
Marketing focus on top revenue-generating categories

Cost optimization through freight and manufacturing analysis

Strategic inventory planning based on sales forecasts

Better financial control by analyzing deduction patterns

⚙️ Tools Used
Power BI Desktop (.pbix file)

DAX for calculated measures and KPIs

Interactive filters and slicers for user-driven exploration

🚀 How to Use
Open the .pbix file in Power BI Desktop

Use slicers to filter by Year, Region, or Category

Hover over visuals for tooltips and deeper insights

Observe forecast projections and KPI cards for quick summaries

🧠 Learnings & Challenges
Learned to handle large datasets and optimize visuals for performance

Gained advanced skills in DAX, visual storytelling, and Power BI layout design

Ensured dashboard aligns with real business questions and decision-making

